This area is bisected by the tidal section of the{River Loughor.}The river also provides the boundary between the counties of{Dyfed}and{West {Glamorgan. }
This area of{Dyfed}was once part of the south east section of the old county of{Carmarthenshire.}The block contains the major part of three communities;{Pontarddulais}on the eastern bank of the river, and{Hendy and{Llangennech}on the western bank.
Tributaries of the{Loughor}enter the main river at all three villages, the {Dulais}at{Pontarddulais,}the{Gwili}at {Hendy}and the{Morlais}at{Llangennech.
